dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Can you describe your main symptoms and how long you have been experiencing them?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: I've been having double vision and muscle weakness for about a month now. It gets harder to climb stairs or brush my hair, especially after I've been active, but I feel better after resting for a while.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any difficulty swallowing, speaking, or breathing, especially when you are tired?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: Yes, sometimes I feel like my speech gets a bit slurred and I have mild trouble swallowing, especially when I’m more tired, but I haven’t had any issues with breathing.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any changes in your facial expressions, such as difficulty smiling or closing your eyes tightly?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: Yes, sometimes I feel like my smile is a bit weaker on long days, and I do have some trouble keeping my eyes tightly shut when I'm tired.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any muscle twitching, cramping, or numbness in your limbs, or is it mainly just weakness that worsens with activity?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: It's mainly just weakness that gets worse the more I use my muscles. I haven't noticed any twitching, cramping, or numbness.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any drooping of your eyelids, especially as the day goes on or when you are tired?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: Yes, I have noticed that my eyelids sometimes droop, especially later in the day or when I feel more tired. It seems to get better after I rest for a while.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you had any recent infections, illnesses, or started any new medications around the time your symptoms began?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: No, I haven’t had any recent infections or illnesses, and I haven’t started any new medications lately.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you or any family members ever been diagnosed with autoimmune diseases or neurological conditions?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: No, neither I nor any of my family members have been diagnosed with autoimmune or neurological conditions as far as I know.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any changes in your vision besides double vision, such as blurry vision or difficulty focusing?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: No, I haven't noticed any blurriness or trouble focusing—it's mainly just seeing double, especially when I'm tired or after using my eyes for a while.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you ever experienced similar symptoms in the past, or is this the first time you’ve had this kind of muscle weakness and double vision?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: This is the first time I’ve had these symptoms. I’ve never experienced muscle weakness or double vision like this before.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: REQUEST TEST: Acetylcholine_Receptor_Antibody_Test

dialogue_history.speaker: Measurement
dialogue_history.text: RESULTS: Acetylcholine Receptor Antibodies: Present (elevated)

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Okay, I have gathered enough information from the patient. I need to analyze this and potentially consult a specialist.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor

dialogue_history.text: I've been having trouble walking for about a week now—my friends say I look like I'm drunk when I try to walk. My balance feels off, and I sometimes stumble or sway.

dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any other symptoms, such as headaches, vision changes, nausea, weakness in your arms or legs, or difficulty speaking?

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any changes in sensation, such as numbness or tingling, in your arms, legs, or face?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: I haven’t really noticed any numbness or tingling, but my right arm does feel weaker than usual. It’s mostly the trouble with walking and keeping my balance that bothers me.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you had any recent infections, fevers, or illnesses before these symptoms started?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: No, I haven't had any recent infections, fevers, or illnesses before these symptoms started.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you ever experienced anything like this before, or do you have any history of neurological conditions such as stroke, multiple sclerosis, or migraines?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: No, I’ve never had anything like this before, and I don’t have any history of neurological conditions like stroke, MS, or migraines. This is all new for me.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any changes in your speech, swallowing, or facial movements, such as drooping or difficulty smiling?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: No, I haven't noticed any changes in my speech or swallowing, and my face seems normal—no drooping or trouble smiling.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you had any recent head injuries, falls, or accidents?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: No, I haven't had any recent head injuries, falls, or accidents. My walking just started getting worse on its own.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any changes in your bladder or bowel control, such as incontinence or difficulty urinating?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: No, I haven’t noticed any changes in my bladder or bowel control. Everything seems normal in that regard.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any tremors, involuntary movements, or stiffness in your arms or legs?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: No, I haven’t noticed any tremors or involuntary movements. My right arm just feels weaker than usual, and I feel unsteady when I try to walk.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed if your symptoms are getting worse, staying the same, or improving over the past week?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: They’ve been getting worse over the past week—I feel more unsteady, and my right arm feels weaker than before.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Okay, I have gathered enough information from the patient. I need to analyze this and potentially consult a specialist.

final_doctor_diagnosis: Cerebellar ataxia (likely due to an acute cerebellar lesion, such as cerebellar stroke or mass)

dialogue_history.text: Did you have any recent injury, fall, or unusual activity before the pain started?

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you been able to walk normally since the pain started, or are you limping or avoiding putting weight on that leg?

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you tried taking any medications or using ice or heat on your knee? If so, did it help with the pain?

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any difficulty fully straightening or bending your knee, or does it feel like your range of motion is limited compared to your other knee?

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Okay, I have gathered enough information from the patient. I need to analyze this and potentially consult a specialist.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Can you describe your main symptoms and how long you have been experiencing them?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: I’ve been feeling tenderness in my lower abdomen, especially around my uterus, and I’ve noticed I’m urinating more frequently. These symptoms started a couple of days after I gave birth. I also feel a bit feverish.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any unusual vaginal discharge, such as a foul odor or change in color, since giving birth?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: I have noticed some vaginal discharge, but I’m not sure if it’s unusual. It doesn’t have a strong foul odor, but it seems a bit heavier than before.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you experienced any chills, shaking, or sweats along with your feverish feeling? And have you had any pain or burning when you urinate?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: I haven’t had any chills, shaking, or sweats, and I don’t feel any pain or burning when I urinate.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you noticed any redness, swelling, or pain around your C-section incision or perineal area if you had a vaginal delivery?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: I had a vaginal delivery, and I do feel some tenderness in my lower abdomen, but I haven’t noticed any redness or swelling around the perineal area.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you had any heavy vaginal bleeding, large blood clots, or a foul-smelling discharge since your delivery?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: No, I haven’t noticed any heavy bleeding or large clots, and there’s no foul smell from my discharge.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you had any pain or tenderness when pressing on your lower abdomen, and does the pain get worse when you move or walk?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: Yes, my lower abdomen feels quite tender, especially when you press on it. The pain does seem to get worse when I move around or try to walk.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you had any issues with your appetite, nausea, or vomiting since your symptoms began? And have you noticed any changes in your bowel movements?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: I haven’t really felt like eating much, but I haven’t had any nausea or vomiting. My bowel movements have been less frequent than usual.

dialogue_history.speaker: Doctor
dialogue_history.text: Have you measured your temperature at home, and if so, what was the highest reading? Also, do you feel generally weak or more tired than usual?

dialogue_history.speaker: Patient
dialogue_history.text: I haven’t measured my temperature at home, but I do feel more tired and weak than usual. I’ve also noticed that I get chills sometimes.
